.TH "rh_string" 9 "rh_string" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rh_string \- provides string descriptors for root hub
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned" rh_string
.BI "(int id "  ","
.BI "struct usb_hcd const *hcd "  ","
.BI "u8 *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "id" 12
the string ID number (0: langids, 1: serial #, 2: product, 3: vendor)
.IP "hcd" 12
the host controller for this root hub
.IP "data" 12
buffer for output packet
.IP "len" 12
length of the provided buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Produces either a manufacturer, product or serial number string for the
virtual root hub device.
.SH "RETURN"
The number of bytes filled in: the length of the descriptor or
of the provided buffer, whichever is less.
